# === Secrets — NEVER commit (defense in depth: patterns + explicit paths) ===
.env
*.env
**/.env
!*.env.example
*.key
*.pem
**/token.json
**/token_cache.json
**/client_secret*.json

# === instance/ = runtime state + LIVE credentials + the agent workspace
#     (its own embedded git repo). Ignore it ALL; track only sanitized examples. ===
instance/*
!instance/config/
instance/config/*
!instance/config/openclaw.json.example
!instance/config/.env.example

# === Python venv / caches / bytecode ===
mcp-mail/.venv/
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# === Databases / vector stores ===
*.db
*.rvf

# === Upstream OpenClaw clone (their repo + their .git — reference only) ===
upstream/

# === Internal working docs / tooling artifacts (not for the public repo) ===
docs/
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
tasks/
MEMORY.md
HANDOFF.md
SECURITY-AUDIT.md
OPENCLAW-TRACK.md
LINKEDIN-POST.md

# === OS cruft ===
.DS_Store
._*
